The educator was shot and killed in Mandalay on Tuesday. CAPE TOWN - Police are investigating the murder of a Kuils River school principal. The educator was shot and killed in Mandalay yesterday afternoon. Spokesperson for the Education MEC Jessica Shelver says: "We understand the incident has really traumatised the learner. Our Safe Schools will assist with trauma counselling for the learner. This was a senseless murder and is deeply tragic. Our thoughts are the teacher's family and school community during this difficult time."